#: ../../W/win.rst:5
msgid "win"
msgstr "win"

#: ../../W/win.rst:7
msgid "[MIT; now common everywhere]"
msgstr "[MIT; 今ではどこでも一般的]"

#: ../../W/win.rst:9
msgid ""
"vi\\. To succeed. A program wins if no unexpected conditions arise, or "
"(especially) if it is sufficiently :ref:`robust` to take exceptions in "
"stride."
msgstr ""
"自動詞。成功すること。プログラムは、予期しない条件が一切生じなければ、あるいは(特に)例外を難なく受け止めるほど十分に\\ "
":ref:`robust`\\ であれば、winする。"

#: ../../W/win.rst:13
msgid ""
"n\\. Success, or a specific instance thereof. A pleasing outcome. \"So it "
"turned out I could use a :ref:`lexer` generator instead of hand-coding my "
"own pattern recognizer. What a win!\" Emphatic forms: moby win, super win, "
"hyper-win (often used interjectively as a reply). For some reason suitable "
"win is also common at MIT, usually in reference to a satisfactory solution "
"to a problem. Oppose :ref:`lose`\\; see also :ref:`big-win`\\, which isn't "
"quite just an intensification of win."
msgstr ""
"名詞。成功、またはその具体的な一例。喜ばしい結果。「結局、自前のパターン認識器を手でコーディングする代わりに\\ :ref:`lexer`\\ "
"ジェネレータを使えることがわかった。なんてwinだ!」。強調形: moby win、super win、hyper-"
"win(しばしば返答として間投詞的に使われる)。何らかの理由でsuitable winもMITでよく使われ、たいていは問題の満足のいく解決を指す。\\ "
":ref:`lose`\\ の反対。\\ :ref:`big-win`\\ も参照。これはwinの単なる強調そのものではない。"
